                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d429">
                <head>No. 423.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Porter</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Valera</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-03-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 25, 1886</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Sill: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of your note of the 12th of
                    March, in which you inclose, with reference to a communication of 2d instant, a
                    copy of a note from the minister of state of Spain, on the subject of the
                    intended encouragement of the American enterprise in the Caroline Islands,
                    having in view the well-being of the native populations there. The minister’s
                    communication is exceedingly satisfactory, and I await with much interest the
                    farther information which your kind note promises the Department.</p>
                <p>Accept, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JAS. D. PORTER,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
